Example with meshfem3d with mesh doubling for staight chunk

Mode used : prem_iso

The mesh of Axisem is made for a 5s dominant

The source (explosive type) has a 10s period

See the Manual for the coupling here : utils/EXTERNAL_CODES_coupled_with_SPECFEM3D/AxiSEM_for_SPECFEM3D/Manual_coupling_AxiSEM_Specfem3D.pdf

See the manual of AxiSEM here : utils/EXTERNAL_CODES_coupled_with_SPECFEM3D/AxiSEM_for_SPECFEM3D/AxiSEM_modif_for_coupling_with_specfem/MANUAL/manual_axisem1.1.pdf

update paths_for_coupling_SPECFEM3D_AxiSEM.sh

TO USE staight chunk you have to do : 

compile meshfem3D with this varaible set to .true. :

line 110 file : src/meshfem3D/save_databases.f90
 logical, parameter :: SAVE_MESH_AS_CUBIT = .true.

fill Par_file : 

# to couple with an external code (such as DSM, AxiSEM, or FK)
COUPLE_WITH_EXTERNAL_CODE       = .true.
EXTERNAL_CODE_TYPE              = 2   # 1 = DSM, 2 = AxiSEM, 3 = FK
TRACTION_PATH                   = ./DATA/AxiSEM_tractions/1/
MESH_A_CHUNK_OF_THE_EARTH       = .true.
RECIPROCITY_AND_KH_INTEGRAL     = .false.

Define mesh : update files  

DATA/meshfem3D_files/Mesh_Par_file
DATA/meshfem3D_files/interfaces.dat

MANDATORY :  choose sequential mode for creating mesh and use scotch for partitionning.

fill ParFileMeshChunk
after run the example the same way that explain in manual 

if need you can define new stations with this script: convert_station_from_geographic_to_cartesian_in_mesh.sh


